lmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs William Lockwood married William Lockwood before 1309, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1294–1341":"1294–1341","1309–1341":"1309–1341","–Female":"Surnud","about 1309":"umbes 1309","1341":"1341","before 1309":"enne 1309","1294":"1294","1309":"1309","England":"England","Lockwood, Yorkshire, England":"Lockwood, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1294–1341":"1294–1341","1309–1341":"1309–1341","–Female":"Kuollut","about 1309":"noin 1309","1341":"1341","before 1309":"ennen vuotta 1309","1294":"1294","1309":"1309","England":"England","Lockwood, Yorkshire, England":"Lockwood, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1294–1341":"1294–1341","1309–1341":"1309–1341","–Female":"Décédée","about 1309":"environ 1309","1341":"1341","before 1309":"avant 1309","1294":"1294","1309":"1309","England":"Angleterre","Lockwood, Yorkshire, England":"Lockwood, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs William Lockwood a épousé William Lockwood avant 1309, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1294–1341":"1294–1341","1309–1341":"1309–1341","–Female":"Verstorben","about 1309":"um 1309","1341":"1341","before 1309":"vor 1309","1294":"1294","1309":"1309","England":"England","Lockwood, Yorkshire, England":"Lockwood, Yorkshire, England","lifeSummary":"Mrs William Lockwood hat vor 1309 in England William Lockwood geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1294–1341":"1294–1341","1309–1341":"1309–1341","–Female":"Desede","about 1309":"about 1309","1341":"13